f=Governance/board/custom/fiduciary-guard/SKILL.md · in=fiduciary-guard board's budget-approval gate. Any spend above configured approval gate gets tested against two financial checks post-spend runway against runway floor, expected ROI against ROI minimum receives recommendation APPROVE, CONDITIONAL, REJECT numbers shown. deterministic arithmetic lives `scripts/fiduciary_check.py`; judgment (what numbers mean, what conditions attach) stays agent, DOE split. skill produces *governance recommendation about spending process* financial advice, thresholds embodying business's risk appetite operator's set. · p=Small businesses die unexamined spending; big ventures die unexamined big spending. skill makes examination automatic consistent: three questions (is above gate? keep above runway floor? clear ROI bar?) asked way spend, whatever threshold levels fit business $1K small Canadian shop, $50K funded venture. skill, different config. · wu=Triggers: "approve budget," "can afford this," "spend approval," "budget gate," automatically any decision board's gate sequence includes spend commitment. for: constitutional never-do's (constitution-enforcement categorical, threshold), strategy-conflict checks (strategic-veto), investment/trading decisions any kind skill gates *operating spend process*, nothing more. · st:/ Protocol=`Load thresholds from config (never defaults, never invented) \· -> Gather the spend facts (amount, one-time vs recurring, expected return, current financials) \· -> Run scripts/fiduciary_check.py (gate check, runway check, ROI check) \· -> Map results to recommendation: APPROVE / CONDITIONAL / REJECT + reason \· -> Log the ruling; escalate per the escalation rule` · h3:Phase Load Thresholds=Read board's config (`operational/agent/board-config.md`): `spend_approval_gate`, `runway_floor_months`, `roi_minimum`. **If any unset, stop ask operator set it** substitute catalog's illustrative values ($5K months 1.5×) any default. Thresholds business's risk appetite; inventing them inventing business's risk appetite. · h3:Phase Gather Spend Facts=**Amount shape**: one-time recurring (monthly). Recurring spend changes burn, cash., **Current financials**: cash hand, monthly burn. configured financials source operator never estimated board., **Expected return**: requester's claimed return horizon, any. credible return estimate exists, ROI check marked EVALUATED, passed. · h3:Phase 3 — Compute=`python scripts/fiduciary_check.py <input.json>            # markdown check table \· python scripts/fiduciary_check.py <input.json> --format json` · h3:Phase 3 — Compute=Build input JSON schema top `scripts/fiduciary_check.py` run: script computes: whether amount clears approval gate; runway before after (one-time: cash amount over burn; recurring: cash over burn monthly amount); ROI (expected return total cost); check's PASS FAIL NOT_EVALUATED. · h3:Phase 4 — Recommend=**Below gate** board approval required; log pass through (note it, don't rubber-stamp silently)., **Above gate, checks PASS** **APPROVE** recommendation, numbers shown., **Above gate, any check FAIL** **REJECT** recommendation, citing failing check numbers. rejected spend return re-scoped (smaller amount, staged tranches, stronger return case)., **Above gate, any check NOT_EVALUATED** **CONDITIONAL**: state exactly what data commitment resolve (e.g., "conditional validated return estimate run pre-mortem revenue assumption"). CONDITIONAL data gap, never soft approve. · h3:Phase 4 — Recommend=recommendation board's input operator's decision operator overrule it, overrule gets logged too. · h3:Phase Log Escalate=Log ruling (amount, checks, recommendation, decision-maker's final call) configured decision log. Spends above config's `board_escalation_multiple` gate (if set) escalate operator regardless check results spends big enough passing arithmetic isn't enough. · of=`## Fiduciary Review: [spend, one line] \·  \· **Thresholds (from config):** gate [X] \· runway floor [Y] months \· ROI min [Z] \·  \· \| Check \| Value \| Threshold \| Result \|` · pr=**No thresholds, gate.** Unset thresholds stop skill; they never defaulted invented., **Recurring spend burn, purchase.** $500/month commitment judged effect runway trajectory, $500 decision., **NOT EVALUATED PASS.** missing return estimate produces CONDITIONAL, never quiet approval., **Numbers shown, always.** recommendation carries computed values operator disagree arithmetic's inputs, conclusion., **Recommend, don't decide.** operator owns final call overrule logged either way., **Not financial advice.** spend-process governance; investment decisions risk-appetite settings belong operator. · f=Thresholds unset stop Phase ask operator fill board-config., Financials (cash/burn) unavailable runway check NOT_EVALUATED CONDITIONAL getting real financials; never estimate them., Python unavailable compute three checks manually formulas above; flag run wasn't script-computed., Requester disputes ROI inputs dispute escalates estimates shown; board doesn't arbitrate revenue forecasts (that's marcus/decision-critic pre-mortem job). · b:with Other board Skills=Runs **after** constitution-enforcement categorical violation makes spend question moot) typically **before** risk-assessment-matrix pre-mortem spend fails arithmetic doesn't need failure-mode workshop)., constitution-enforcement owns categorical never-do's; skill owns tunable thresholds. "rule" keeps needing exceptions migrates here, config constitution., pre-mortem CONDITIONAL's shaky return assumption goes get tested., Boundary marcus: venture-priority-matrix ranks competing spends pool *before* proposals form; fiduciary-guard gates specific proposed spend *after*.